HOUSTON (AP) _ Callon Petroleum Co. (CPE) on Wednesday reported fourth-quarter net income of $285.4 million, after reporting a loss in the same period a year earlier.On a per-share basis, the Houston-based company said it had net income of $4.78. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring gains, were $2.66 per share.The results did not meet Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $2.81 per share.The independent oil and gas company posted revenue of $692.2 million in the period, surpassing Street forecasts. Four analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $526.3 million.For the year, the company reported net income of $365.2 million, or $7.26 per share, swinging to a profit in the period. Revenue was reported as $2.05 billion._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on CPE at https://www.zacks.com/ap/CPE